helpdesk-ticket.subject: Conference Telephone in Schroeder Room
helpdesk-ticket.description: Hi Support, We have had two complaints about the conference telephone in the Schroeder Room. In one complaint, a member of a thesis committee who was located in Ohio was given the telephone number of the Schroeder Room conference phone and was instructed to call in. He did call in, and the telephone indicated that he was connected, but it was not possible to hear him. The thesis committee people in the Schroeder Room then attempted to call him with the conference phone, but once again, it was not possible for us to hear him. He was eventually called on a cell phone, and he confirmed that when he called into the Schroeder Room and when he was called from the Schroeder Room, he could not hear any voices through the connection. We have received one other complaint indicating that the phone "doesn't work." It's possible someone forgot to press a button, or pressed the wrong button, but when someone has a chance, would they please check the conference phone? Thanks, Gary Shimek Director of the Library
helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
Hi Support,

We have had two complaints about the conference telephone in the Schroeder Room.  In one complaint, a member of a thesis committee who was located in Ohio was given the telephone number of the Schroeder Room conference phone and was instructed to call in.  He did call in, and the telephone indicated that he was connected, but it was not possible to hear him. The thesis committee people in the Schroeder Room then attempted to call him with the conference phone, but once again, it was not possible for us to hear him.  He was eventually called on a cell phone, and he confirmed that when he called into the Schroeder Room and when he was called from the Schroeder Room, he could not hear any voices through the connection.  We have received one other complaint indicating that the phone "doesn't work."  It's possible someone forgot to press a button, or pressed the wrong button, but when someone has a chance, would they please check the conference phone?

Thanks,

Gary Shimek
Director of the Library

helpdesk-ticket.description-html:
I got a popup notifying me my password expires in 7 days.

Attached are two emails that we have received just today from people unable to log into their http://myfinancialaid.msoe.edu account. 
 
Any immediate assistance would be greatly appreciated as this issue reaches the vast majority of our current student population.
 
Thanks,
Heather Cooper
 
 
 
From: helpdesk [mailto:helpdesk@msoe.edu]
Sent: Thursday, May 12, 2016 9:18 AM
To: Cooper, Heather <cooperh@msoe.edu>
Subject: Re: [#INC-7981] Financial Aid NetPartner
 
Hi Heather Cooper,
 
The screenshot that you sent us seems more like a network connection problem than an account problem. If you could send these students to our helpdesk on the 3rd floor of the CC building, we can address these issues more accurately.

Issue: http://helpdesk.msoe.edu/helpdesk/tickets/7981
 
Hello-
 
We have had a large number of returning students stating that they are unable to get to the http://myfinancialaid.msoe.edu page let alone be able to log in. 
 
Kyle Brown is an example of who cannot log in.  I hope this helps.
 
Thanks,
 
Heather Cooper
Assistant Director
MSOE Financial Aid
1025 N Broadway
Milwaukee, WI  53202
414-277-7222
 
Follow us on the MSOE Community!!
 
 
 
 
Thanks,
Michael Logan

414-277-7288

Thanks,
 
Heather Cooper

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Senior with freshman year computer and paid technology fees
helpdesk-ticket.description:

helpdesk-note.body:
Hey Natalie,
We are sorry to hear that your current laptop is not performing well. You have a few options.
You can keep your current laptop and have us fix the various issues you are having with it. Most of your problems will be solved with a visit to the Helpdesk. You will then graduate and keep the 8560w. (We also have other 8560w to swap you into if needed). You can upgrade to a ZBook 15 G1, which would also fix your various laptop issues. You would then graduate and keep the G1.
To answer your second question, there will be no refunds for past technology fees. The technology fee covers more than simply the laptop price and cannot be refunded unless due to a mistaken assignment, (which is not the case now because you have been full time since 2013).
Have a great day!

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Digital Signage System - Industry Weapon MediaBridge Update
helpdesk-ticket.description: It is my understanding that Industry Weapon has been trying to contact the MSOE IT department regarding an upcoming upgrade to MediaBridge, which is part of our digital signage system. I am passing along the email they sent to me about it yesterday: "Due to recent changes to our security requirements Industry Weapon is looking to deploy an improved version of the Virtual MediaBridge currently used with your CCHD solution. This new MediaBridge+ allows us to maintain support against the latest network vulnerabilities. We are looking to have this upgrade completed by the end of June 2016. I see that you are currently using a physical appliance to host your Industry Weapon MediaBridge. To that end, there are three options to consider when upgrading. 1) Move to a virtual appliance. Industry Weapon offers both a VMware and Hyper-V option that can function as a MediaBridge. These images are offered free of charge to replace your physical appliance. Please contact support@industryweapon.com if you are interested in this path. 2) Acquire a branded Industry Weapon USB stick that will automatically re-image your physical appliance to the MediaBridge+ release.* Please contact accountteam@industryweapon.com if you are interested in this path. 3) If you are familiar with device imaging, we are offering the specific images developed for the various hardware platforms we support. Please contact support@industryweapon.com if you are interested in this path. If you have any questions, please contact 877-607-0562, or email us at support@industryweapon.com. *These options will include some downtime, as once the re-image is complete, your appliance will be in a factory state and require setup."

2) Acquire a branded Industry Weapon USB stick that will automatically re-image your physical appliance to the MediaBridge+ release.* Please contact accountteam@industryweapon.com if you are interested in this path.

helpdesk-ticket.subject: 3F0 no boot device found on 840G2 37540
helpdesk-ticket.description: Tori Hanson came to the desk with a black screen error message on her 840G2 stating 3F0 boot device not found. Ran a hard drive test and the drive failed. I tried to read the drive using an external reader and because the master boot record is missing, it cannot mount the partitions. I used the windows boot disk to try and fix the master boot record using bootrec /fixmbr command. This returns the error message that a device attached to this system is not working. I tried placing the failed drive in the freezer for 2 hours and retried to fix the master boot record and it still failed. I am unable to recover any data.
helpdesk-ticket.description-html: Tori Hanson came to the desk with a black screen error message on her 840G2 stating 3F0 boot device not found.  Ran a hard drive test and the drive failed.  I tried to read the drive using an external reader and because the master boot record is missing, it cannot mount the partitions.  I used the windows boot disk to try and fix the master boot record using bootrec /fixmbr command.  This returns the error message that a device attached to this system is not working.  I tried placing the failed drive in the freezer for 2 hours and retried to fix the master boot record and it still failed.  I am unable to recover any data.

helpdesk-note.body:
Richard,
If you are just trying to use the Thunderbird app, I downloaded it here: https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/thunderbird/
After you install Thunderbird, run it. You should get a page that looks like this:
Select "Skip this and use my existing email"
This page should be next.
Enter your information. Click Continue. You should see this next:
Select "Manual config"
Change both server hostnames to outlook.com. Keep the other settings at their default. Make sure it matches this picture and then select Done. This should work. Let us know if this does not work for you.
Have a great day!
helpdesk-note.body-html:
Richard,

If you are just trying to use the Thunderbird app, I downloaded it here: https://www.mozilla.org/en-US/thunderbird/

After you install Thunderbird, run it. You should get a page that looks like this:

Select "Skip this and use my existing email"

This page should be next.
Enter your information. Click Continue.
You should see this next:
Select "Manual config"
Change both server hostnames to outlook.com. Keep the other settings at their default. Make sure it matches this picture and then select Done. 
This should work. Let us know if this does not work for you.

Have a great day!

helpdesk-note.body:
Hi Joseph,
Microsoft Project can be obtained through Microsoft dreamspark. Currently dreamspark accounts are only available for select majors on campus and I do believe your department has a dreamspark account. In the fall of 2015 an email was sent out to students who were a part of the select departments on campus that have access to dreamspark. Your first step should be to check your school email and look through your mailboxes for it. This email will walk you through the steps of activating your dreamspark account. If you can't find this email in your mailboxes then I would advise you to talk to faculty in your department who have experience with dreamspark.
Here is a link to a thread on MSOE community that should provide some background information on registering your dreamspark account. https://community.msoe.edu/thread/4811
Let me know if you have anymore questions or if I can do anything else to help.
Best, Sam West MSOE IT

helpdesk-ticket.subject: Lawrence Gardner Outlook Connection Issue
helpdesk-ticket.description:
Coach Gardner had an issue with Outlook not updating his inbox and not sending any emails (they would hang in outbox). I noticed that it was due to a recent password change and Credential Manager not updating with the password. Coach Gardner is using Windows 10, so I just searched for Credential Manager in the Start Menu search. I found his email credential under "Windows Credentials" and in the subcategory "Generic Credentials". We deleted the old credential, reopened Outlook, and he was able to successfully connect after typing his new password.
This ticket is meant as a record for IT, no need to respond. However, if you ever need to reach IT our extension is 7288. (414-277-7288).
Have a great day!
